obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_155  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This publication assigns Collybistin immunoreactivity clearly to a subset of inhibitory synapses throughout the brain. Collybistin is an established interactor of Gephyrin, which was localized to the inhibitory postsynapse through immunogold as reviewed in 24552784.\n\n10/2/2017 Pim\nNote: clusters of gephyrin, a postsynaptic protein, are used in this publication as a proxy for inh. synapses (see PMID:24552784).\nFig.2: inh. (GABA) synapses in cerebellar ctx [rat]\nFig.3: inh. (GABA) synapses in purkinje cells [mouse]\nFig.4: various brain area's in brain [rat]\nFig.5: colocalization with different GABA-A-R subunits in various brain area's, and with GlycRs in brainstem [rat]\nMy final interpretation is that CB3 is present in the postsynaptic specialization (using gephyrin as a proxy) of GABA-ergic and Glycin-ergic synapses in the rodent brain (as also indicated by the Gundelfinger group).. Experimental description: This study was performed on adult (4-8 weeks old) Wistar rats (n=14) and C57BL/6J mice (n=5) of both sexes.\n\n10/2/2017 Pim: anntotation against Rat approved." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_155" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

